    • Method Detail

      • beginInsert

        void beginInsert()
                 throws Exception
        Initializes the data import for this ImporterEngine instance. This method must be invoked before calling the addDataRow() method.
        Throws:
        Exception - if any error occurs.

      • end

        void end()
         throws Exception
        Finalizes the current data import. This method has to be invoked after finishing the data import.
        Throws:
        Exception - if any error occurs.

      • setConfiguration

        void setConfiguration(Match_data data)
        Provides the configuration for this importer instance. Since the engine is configured by the importer system there is no need to call this method manually.
        Parameters:
        data - - the configuration for this importer instance

      • truncateNamespace

        void truncateNamespace()
                       throws Exception
        Truncates the current namespace.
        In fact, no data will be deleted, tables are swapped instead.
        Throws:
        Exception - if any error occurs.

      • refresh

        void refresh()
             throws Exception
        Refreshes the current namespace.
        Throws:
        Exception - if any error occurs

      • reload

        void reload(boolean incremental)
            throws Exception
        Imports new data configured by given Match_MakerData.
        Parameters:
        data - the configuration for this import operation
        incremental - determines whether the data should be appended or not
        Throws:
        Exception - if any error occurs

      • done

        void done()
          throws Exception
        Causes the engine to stop the current import action, and cleans up any unused data.
        This method should be called after inserting, updating or deleting data has been finished.
        Throws:
        Exception - if any error occurs
